description: There is a lot of talk in the past two days about this area around Vysokopillya and the supposed "encirclement". First
column4: I want to state that on July 8th Ukraine came out and said that over 90% of the structures in this town have been demolished (I have the ruins marker).

WKT: I actually created the ruins marker in response to this report. BTW. A brief aside
name: but I think it is related an incredibly interesting. Velyka Oleksandrivka is also said to be almost entirely destroyed
description: and this is a Russian controlled. Meaning Ukrainian artillery did the damage

name: the town is almost entirely destroyed and has been for weeks. As a result
description: the town has almost certainly been a gray area under the control of neither Russia nor Ukraine. There is nothing to defend! Nothing to control.

WKT: Olhyne is almost certainly in a similar situation
name: and it has been a gray area as well. So
description: ask yourself
column4: why would Russia push thousands of men into a totally destroyed town? What would they even do there? The story doesn't make any sense to me.

name: I think this is a convenient misinformation from Ukraine. Who started spreading the story
description: I do not know
column4: but I think it is being used to cover for what is actually happening. For example
column5: those smaller attacks into Andriivka (16) and Bilohirka (15).

name: perhaps
description: it is covering for a larger attack on Arkhanhelske
column4: which is in a precarious position on the Russian line. And rumors of encirclement mention Arkhanhelske as well. In fact
column5: if you told me the encirclement were there

name: for sure
description: Ukraine absolutely advanced forward toward Olhyne (14)
column4: and I believe there is a strong chance they have turned this gray area blue. But that doesn't change the fact that these towns have been rubblized.
